19/08/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Sarajevo's municipal court Tuesday (August 18th) fined Italian bank Intesa Sanpaolo and its local branch director, Almir Krkalic, for illegally raising interest rates.
The bank is to pay 4,100 euros.
The lawsuit was filed by a bank customer who borrowed 17,000 euros.
The court has opened 192 similar cases against Intensa Sanpaolo and nine other banks operating in BiH.
(Dnevni Avaz, BHRT, Srna, Oslobodjenje, Fena - 18/08/09)
